The course includes the following topics: Estonian folklore and ealier school literature; Estonian children's literature and the development of critical thought; Estonian children's poetry, modern children's literature.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge of the history, theory and classics of Estonian children's literature necessary for teaching at primary school. To foster students' understanding of a child's emotinal world with the help of children's literature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student will have basic knowledge of Estonian literature and the theory of children's literature; analyses literary works and is able to espress the results, is able to connect literature with real life contexts; can apply acquired knowledge in teaching different subjects and extra-curricular activities.
